Package pl.edu.agh.kis.pz1.util

Class Gameplay

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.edu.agh.kis.pz1.util.Gameplay
  • public class Gameplay
extends java.lang.Object
    Class providing smooth Game Phases transition when certain conditions are satisfied. List of gamePhases: 1 - pay Ante and get cards 2 - first Bid 3 - exchange cards 4 - second Bid 5 - evaluate Hands and under 'winner' command there will be winner / restart game by voting with 'restart' command

    • Method Detail

      • passPhase1

        public static void passPhase1​(Player p)
        Method used for grouping players who have taken their cards from the table. When all players take their cards GamePhase is incremented. Then second GamePhase comes - it is first Bet phase.
        Parameters:
        p - Add player to the phase1 set when Player takes cards from the table ('get cards' command)

      • passPhase2

        public static void passPhase2​(Player p)
        The method provides handling first Bet phase in the game (Second GamePhase). Second phase is passed when all bets are equal, not 0 and queue has accomplished full cycle (first player at the beginning of the cycle is the first player). In simple words when all Players meet in the same bet value. To check if all players' Bet values are equal is used HashMap in which Players and their Bet values are stored.
        Parameters:
        p - Add player to the phase2 HashMap when Player places a Bet

      • passPhase3

        public static void passPhase3​(Player p)
        Method used for grouping players who have exchanged their cards. When all players exchange their cards GamePhase is incremented. Then fourth GamePhase comes - it is second Bet phase.
        Parameters:
        p - Add player to the phase3 set when Player takes cards from the table ('get cards' command)

      • passPhase4

        public static void passPhase4​(Player p)
        The method provides handling second Bet phase in the game (Fourth GamePhase). Fourth phase is passed when all bets are equal, not 0 and queue has accomplished full cycle (first player at the beginning of the cycle is the first player). In simple words when all Players meet in the same bet value. To check if all players' Bet values are equal is used HashMap in which Players and their Bet values are stored.
        Parameters:
        p - Add player to the phase4 HashMap when Player places a Bet

      • checkBetStatus

        public static void checkBetStatus​(Player p,
                                  java.util.HashMap<Player,​java.lang.Integer> bets)
        Method used for Bet handling. Checks if queue accomplished full cycle and all players' bet values are equal (and not 0).
        Parameters:
        p - Player placing bet
        bets - HashMap containing Players with their bet values
